  "texts": [
    "The MMR pathway detects O 6 mG:T mismatches and removes the mis-paired thymine residues 13, 14.",
    "However, the O 6 mG lesion persists and MMR-mediated gap-filling reforms the O 6 mG:T mis-pair resulting in additional futile MMR cycles [15] [16] [17] [18] [19].",
    "The precise mechanism by which MMR futile cycling leads to cytotoxicity has yet to be established.",
    "A widely favoured model posits that the long single-stranded DNA (ssDNA) gaps generated by futile MMR cycles interfere with DNA replication forks 20, 21.",
    "However, the specific DNA repair and DNA replication fork-protective mechanisms that allow GBM to tolerate TMZinduced lesions remain poorly characterized."
  ],
